============================================
XSSer - Cross Site Scripter - "The Mosquito"
============================================

XSSer is an open source penetration testing tool that automates the process of detecting and exploiting XSS injections against different applications.

Website: 

- http://xsser.sourceforge.net/

Community:

- lorea.org: https://n-1.cc/pg/groups/15466/xsser/
- identi.ca: http://identi.ca/group/xsser
- twitter: https://twitter.com/lord_epsylon/xsser

===================
HOW-TO INSTALL:
===================

XSSer runs on many platforms.  It requires Python and the following libraries:

- python-pycurl - Python bindings to libcurl
- python-beautifulsoup - error-tolerant HTML parser for Python
- python-xml - XML tools for Python

On Debian-based systems, run: 

sudo apt-get install python-pycurl python-beautifulsoup python-xml

Please report any problems you encounter using XSSer to the xsser-users mailing-list:

- mailto:xsser-users@lists.sourceforge.net

Or write directly to:

- root@lordepsylon.net / epsylon@riseup.net



